The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Geometric to split shares

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, April 14: Geometric Software Solutions will split its stock in the ratio of 1:5. Consequently, its shares with a face value of Rs 10 apiece will be sub-divided into five shares of Rs 2 each.

 The stock split is expected to make the share more affordable to retail investors. The company has declared a dividend of Rs 4 per share.

 The Geometric share closed at Rs 508.30 on the Bombay Stock Exchange yesterday. While promoters hold a 31.17 per cent stake in the company, institutional investors own 24.79 per cent. Retail investors hold 29.09 per cent shares, private corporate bodies 4.33 per cent and NRIs/OCBs own the rest.

 Geometric has reported a 44 per cent rise in net profit for the fourth quarter ended March 31 at Rs 5.55 crore compared with Rs 3.86 crore in the corresponding period last year.

 Total income has increased to Rs 31.67 crore in the fourth quarter from Rs 20.35 crore in the year-ago period. 

 In 2004-05, the company posted a net profit of Rs 20.66 crore (Rs 16.66 crore). Total income increased to Rs 106.26 crore from Rs 73.44 crore in 2003-04.

 On a consolidated basis, the group recorded a net profit of Rs 8.09 crore for the quarter compared with Rs 5.34 crore in the year-ago period. Total income was Rs 52.51 crore against Rs 32.03 crore in the fourth quarter of the year ended March 2004. 




